# Copy to .env (gitignored) for local dev. Defaults match docker-compose.yml so that
#   cp .env.example .env && docker compose up -d && pnpm db:migrate
# works with zero edits. Real secrets never go in this committed example.

# --- Postgres: OWNER/superuser connection ---
# Used by the migrator (src/db/migrate.ts) and drizzle-kit for DDL: CREATE EXTENSION,
# tables, RLS policies, GRANTs. Owns the schema.
# NOTE: 127.0.0.1, not localhost — on Windows, Node may resolve localhost to IPv6 (::1)
# first, but Docker publishes the port on IPv4, giving a spurious ECONNREFUSED.
DATABASE_URL=postgres://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:5432/memos

# --- Postgres: least-privileged APP role (Phase 1+) ---
# The gateway connects as memos_app (a NON-owner, NON-superuser role) at runtime so
# that Row-Level Security policies actually apply. Superusers/table-owners BYPASS RLS,
# so the API must NOT use DATABASE_URL. The memos_app role is created in 0000_prereqs.sql.
MEMOS_APP_DATABASE_URL=postgres://memos_app:memos_app@127.0.0.1:5432/memos

# --- MinIO / S3 (artifact blob store, Phase 3+) ---
MINIO_ENDPOINT=http://127.0.0.1:9000
MINIO_ROOT_USER=minioadmin
MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD=minioadmin
MINIO_BUCKET=memos-artifacts
MINIO_REGION=us-east-1

# --- Redis (rate limiting / async workers, Phase 6+) ---
REDIS_URL=redis://127.0.0.1:6379

# --- Web dashboard (Phase 7) ---
# The Next.js operator console (packages/web) reads these (put them in packages/web/.env.local).
# It calls the gateway server-side as the seeded OPERATOR agent — the token is NEVER exposed to
# the browser (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix). MEMOS_OPERATOR_TOKEN must match what `pnpm db:seed` used.
MEMOS_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8787
MEMOS_OPERATOR_TOKEN=syn_demo_operator_0000000000000000
MEMOS_PROJECT_ID=project.demo
SESSION_SECRET=dev-insecure-secret-change-me   # signs the demo login cookie
DEMO_PASSWORD=memos                            # operator login password (demo gate)

# --- Misc ---
MEMOS_LOG_LEVEL=debug

# --- Production (hosted) notes — see docs/DEPLOY.md ---
# These local defaults target docker-compose. In production (Neon + Render + Vercel):
#  - the host injects PORT; server.ts honors PORT first, then MEMOS_PORT, then 8787.
#  - managed Postgres URLs (DATABASE_URL / MEMOS_APP_DATABASE_URL) must end with ?sslmode=require.
#  - MEMOS_OPERATOR_TOKEN must be IDENTICAL on the API host and the dashboard (it seeds + authenticates
#    the operator agent). Generate one strong value and paste it in both places.
#  - the blob store (MINIO_*) is OPTIONAL in prod — only live artifact.upload needs it.

# --- Embeddings (Phase 4 stretch: pgvector embed-on-write) ---
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
